# Development experience ÔÇö dev seed data

Local dev must let a human click through every user-facing surface without manual DB work. That dataset lives in [`src/main/resources/dev-import.sql`](../../src/main/resources/dev-import.sql).

## How it loads

- **Profile:** `%dev` only ÔÇö [`DatabaseDevSetup`](../../src/main/java/dev/vepo/contraponto/shared/infra/DatabaseDevSetup.java) runs the script on every startup.
- **Fresh DB:** `%dev.quarkus.flyway.clean-at-start=true` resets schema + migration seed (admin, footer custom pages), then `dev-import.sql` repopulates content.
- **Run:** `./mvnw quarkus:dev` ÔåÆ [http://localhost:8080](http://localhost:8080) ([README](../../README.md)).

## When adding or changing a feature

Treat `dev-import.sql` as part of the same change as endpoint + template (see [ARCHITECTURE.md](../../ARCHITECTURE.md) ┬ğ9). Before marking work done, confirm you can **see and exercise** the feature in dev without extra steps.

| If the feature involvesÔÇĞ | Seed should includeÔÇĞ |
|--------------------------|----------------------|
| New table / aggregate | At least one row a logged-in user can open from normal navigation |
| New role or permission | A dev user with that role (see existing cast below) |
| New post/publication state | A post in that state (draft, published, republish history, featured, etc.) |
| Audience / notifications | `tb_blog_audience` + sample `tb_notifications` where relevant |
| Editor-only flows (`/review`, featured) | `editor` user + `featured` posts |
| Multi-blog URLs | A secondary blog (e.g. bobÔÇÖs `architecture-notes`) |
| Tags / series / RSS / search | Tagged posts, series membership, enough volume to paginate if applicable |

If migration seed already covers it (e.g. global footer **custom pages** in `V0.0.1__Initial_schema.sql`), extend `dev-import.sql` only when dev needs **additional** examples.

## Script structure (follow existing sections)

1. **Reset** ÔÇö `TRUNCATE` / `DELETE` dev content; keep `admin` user, admin blog, and migration-seeded globals. **Never** `TRUNCATE tb_images CASCADE` ÔÇö inbound FKs from `tb_users` / `tb_blogs` (profile/banner) will wipe admin. See [dev-import-sql-safety.mdc](dev-import-sql-safety.mdc).
2. **Users & roles** ÔÇö fixed personas (do not rename casually; tests/docs may refer to them).
3. **Blogs ÔåÆ images ÔåÆ series ÔåÆ tags ÔåÆ posts ÔåÆ publications** ÔÇö large block uses `DO $$ ÔÇĞ END $$` with variables for FK wiring.
4. **Audience, notifications, views** ÔÇö social/engagement samples.

Add a numbered section comment (`-- ============================================`) when introducing a new block.

## Conventions

- **Passwords:** all dev users use the **same bcrypt hash as `admin`** (see file header). Log in as any seeded username with the admin password.
- **Prefer stable slugs/usernames** (`alice`, `introduction-to-distributed-systems-java`) so URLs are predictable in manual testing and docs.
- **Use subqueries** (`INSERT ÔÇĞ SELECT ÔÇĞ JOIN tb_users u ON u.username = 'alice'`) instead of hard-coded numeric IDs.
- **Respect FK order** when adding tables; extend the reset section if you truncate new content tables.
- **Publishing model:** published posts need `tb_post_publications` rows and `live_publication_id` set like production (see existing version-history examples).
- **Do not** rely on `dev-import.sql` in tests ÔÇö use `Given` builders ([contraponto-tests.mdc](contraponto-tests.mdc)).

## Dev personas (reference)

| Username | Roles | Typical use |
|----------|-------|-------------|
| `admin` | ADMIN, USER_ADMINISTRATOR | Platform admin, `/users`, welcome post |
| `editor` | USER, EDITOR | Featured curation `/review` |
| `alice`, `bob`, `carol` | USER | Authors; main + secondary blogs |
| `dave` | USER | Follower, notification recipient |
| `eve` | USER | Email subscriber (mock mailer in dev) |

## Checklist before finishing

- [ ] Restarted `./mvnw quarkus:dev` (or full reload) and script ran without SQL errors
- [ ] Opened the new/changed UI as the right persona (anonymous vs author vs editor vs admin)
- [ ] Linked navigation reaches the seed data (home, blog, post, library, manage surfaces ÔÇö not only a raw ID in Dev UI)

## Never

- Ship a user-facing feature with **only** empty states in dev (no seed rows).
- Put secrets or production credentials in `dev-import.sql`.
- Break the admin/migration baseline (truncating `tb_users` for `admin`, or deleting migration custom pages).
- Use `TRUNCATE tb_images CASCADE` or any truncate that cascades into `tb_users` / `tb_blogs`.
